chat_history.content: Did you know that the first computer programmer was a woman named Ada Lovelace? She worked on Charles Babbage's Analytical Engine in the mid-1800s and is credited with writing the first algorithm intended to be processed by a machine. Pretty cool, right?
I'm glad you liked it! Do you want to learn any other fun facts?
